    "document": "Function: conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any\nSummary: 4x2 tiled GEMM kernel (v4) replaces 2x2/M4 for small-channel convolutions\nApproach: 4-channel x 2-pixel tiling with LMUL=M2 instead of 2x2/M4. Processes 4 output channels in inner loop, 2 pixels in outer unroll.\nCycles before: baseline v2 kernel\nSpeedup: 3.09x (vs 2.47x for v2)\nPipeline insight: M2 reduces VRF write-back stages vs M4. 4-channel tiling better utilizes VMAC units without register spill.\nLesson: For out_tensor_ch <= 64, smaller LMUL with more tiling gives better results than larger LMUL. Register pressure is the bottleneck, not compute.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: gemm, tiling, lmul, register-pressure, convolution",
