    "id": "4f167833",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_maxpool_HWC_s8\nSummary: Unrolled k_x by 2 to interleave vle8/vmax \u2014 REGRESSED\nApproach: Unrolled inner k_x loop by 2, loading into V8 and V16, then vmaxing both against V0. Goal was to interleave loads and computation to hide load-to-use latency.\nCycles before: 25657\nCycles after: 26489\nSpeedup: 0.97x (3.2% regression)\nPipeline insight: vsim too slow to complete; regression suggests extra pointer arithmetic and register pressure outweigh any load-interleaving benefit. The AX45MPV VLSU may already pipeline sequential vle8/vmax well at M8 e8.\nLesson: For maxpool with M8 e8 loads at VLEN=1024, unrolling the k_x loop by 2 does NOT help. The extra address computation overhead outweighs any load-to-use latency hiding. The original tight loop (vle8 + vmax per iteration) is already efficient for this pattern.\nOutcome: regressed\nTags: maxpool, unroll, load-interleave, regression",
