    "id": "1b35bf81",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast\nSummary: Replaced ENA_TILING GEMM (vectorize col2=32, 12.5% VL util) with im2col + 4x2 GEMM using vd4dots (vectorize K=1152, ~100% VL util)\nApproach: The ENA_TILING path used nn_mat_mul_kernel_tiling_q7 which vectorized across output channels (col2=32). At VLEN=1024/M2, only 32 of 256 possible elements were used per vector op (12.5% utilization). Replaced with the im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft path which uses 4x2 tiled GEMM with vd4dots vectorizing across the reduction dimension K=1152, achieving full VL utilization. Also eliminated the weight transpose step.\nCycles before: 2292500\nCycles after: 551979\nSpeedup: 4.15x\nPipeline insight: vsim timed out. Assembly analysis: inner loop 6 vle8 + 8 vd4dots (M2), ratio 1.33. Speedup from vectorizing K=1152 instead of col2=32.\nLesson: When out_tensor_ch is small relative to VLEN, the tiling GEMM that vectorizes across output channels wastes VL capacity. Switch to GEMM that vectorizes across the reduction dimension K instead. The existing nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft already implements this correctly. Also: ENA_TILING is defined in internal_nn_math.h, not build.sh \u2014 always verify active code path from linked binary objdump.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: conv_HWC, sym_bias_fast, GEMM, tiling, vector-utilization, vd4dots, ENA_TILING",
