    "id": "2afa80a1",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast\nSummary: Switched im2col from 2-pixel to 4-pixel batching with _unroll4 GEMM (4x4/M1) \u2014 4.3% improvement over round 1\nApproach: Changed buffer threshold from 2*K to 4*K and switched GEMM from nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft (4x2/M2) to _unroll4 (4x4/M1). Halves weight reloads, improves compute-to-load ratio from 1.33 to 2.0. Trade-off: M1 gives VL=128 instead of M2 VL=256, doubling inner loop iterations. Net effect: instruction count increased 13% but IPC improved 0.59->0.70, reducing cycles by 4.3%.\nCycles before: 551979\nCycles after: 529123\nSpeedup: 1.043x (4.33x total from baseline 2292500)\nPipeline insight: IPC improved 0.59->0.70, suggesting better instruction-level parallelism from 4x4 tiling. But instruction count increased 13% due to M1 vs M2. Net gain modest.\nLesson: For conv with small out_ch and large K, switching from 4x2/M2 to 4x4/M1 gives modest 4% gain. The higher compute-to-load ratio (2.0 vs 1.33) helps IPC but the doubled inner iterations partially offset. Diminishing returns at this point.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: conv_HWC, sym_bias_fast, GEMM, unroll4, 4x4-tiling, M1-vs-M2",
