    "id": "243fb837",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_fast\nSummary: Replaced ENA_TILING GEMM (vectorize col2=32, 12.5% VL util) with im2col + 4x4 vd4dots GEMM (vectorize K=1152, ~100% VL util)\nApproach: Same optimization as sym_bias_fast: removed weight transpose + tiling GEMM, replaced with 4-pixel im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_2sft_unroll4. K=1152 (128ch*3*3ker) vectorized at VLEN=1024/M1 gives ~4.5 inner loop iterations per output channel group.\nCycles before: 2276133\nCycles after: 522521\nSpeedup: 4.36x\nPipeline insight: Inner loop: 8 vle8 + 16 vd4dots (4x4 tiling, compute-to-load 2.0). Post: 16 vredsum + 12 vslideup + quantization. IPC 0.69, 362K instructions.\nLesson: The ENA_TILING GEMM pattern is consistently ~4x slower than im2col + vd4dots GEMM for these conv functions. The fix is mechanical: replace tiling path with im2col + _2sft/_bias_2sft unroll4 GEMM. Works for both bias and no-bias variants.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: conv, gemm, vd4dots, tiling, VL-utilization, sym_fast",
