    "id": "2369f56c",
    "document": "Function: conv_HWC (general pattern)\nSummary: ENA_TILING GEMM is consistently ~4x slower than im2col + vd4dots GEMM for conv_HWC functions \u2014 mechanical fix pattern\nApproach: All conv_HWC_s8 variants using the ENA_TILING path (nn_mat_mul_kernel_tiling_*) vectorize across output channels (col2, typically 32). At VLEN=1024, this wastes 87.5% of vector length. The fix: replace with im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_*_2sft_unroll4 which vectorizes across the reduction dimension K (in_ch * ker_h * ker_w). Use _bias_2sft_unroll4 for bias variants, _2sft_unroll4 for no-bias. Buffer 4 pixels of im2col before calling the GEMM. Handle leftovers with 2-pixel (_2sft) and 1-pixel (scalar) fallbacks. Remove weight transpose (nn_mat_mul_kernel_tiling_transpose_q7) and intermediate q32 buffer. Proven on: sym_bias_fast (4.33x), sym_fast (4.36x), asym_bias_any (already done).\nCycles before: ~2.3M (typical for 22x22x128->20x20x32, ker=3x3)\nCycles after: ~520K\nSpeedup: ~4.3x consistently\nPipeline insight: Optimized inner loop: 8 vle8 + 16 vd4dots (4x4 tiling), compute-to-load ratio 2.0. IPC ~0.69-0.70. At this point diminishing returns \u2014 Round 2 attempts on sym_bias_fast only yielded 4.3% additional.\nLesson: Any conv_HWC function still using ENA_TILING path with nn_mat_mul_kernel_tiling_* is a guaranteed ~4x win. The fix is mechanical: swap GEMM kernel, adjust buffer sizing, remove weight transpose. Check linked binary objdump for tiling_* calls to identify targets. Remaining candidates: sym_bias_fast_any, sym_fast_any, RGB variants, sft_bias.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: conv, gemm, vd4dots, tiling, VL-utilization, pattern, mechanical-fix",
