    "id": "6ef161b2",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_u8_u8_s8_sym_bias_fast\nSummary: Replaced ENA_TILING GEMM with im2col + 4x4 vd4dotsu GEMM for u8 variant \u2014 3.91x speedup\nApproach: Same mechanical pattern as s8 variants: removed weight transpose + tiling GEMM (nn_mat_mul_kernel_tiling_bias_u8_u8_s8, vectorizes col2=32, 12.5% VL util at VLEN=1024), replaced with 4-pixel im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_u8_bias_2sft_unroll4 (4x4 vd4dotsu, vectorizes K=1152). u8-specific: vd4dotsu for signed*unsigned dot product, vnclipu for [0,255] clipping, NDS_ISA_SAT for scalar fallback.\nCycles before: 2297409\nCycles after: 586975\nSpeedup: 3.91x\nPipeline insight: Inner loop: 8 vle8 + 16 vd4dotsu (M1), compute-to-load 2.0. Same structure as s8 kernel. IPC 0.67.\nLesson: The ENA_TILING to vd4dots/vd4dotsu GEMM pattern extends mechanically to u8 variants. Use nn_mat_mul_kernel_u8_bias_2sft_unroll4 (vd4dotsu) for signed weights * unsigned inputs. vnclipu for unsigned output clipping. All conv_HWC u8 variants with ENA_TILING should follow the same pattern.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: conv_HWC, u8, ENA_TILING, vd4dotsu, GEMM, mechanical_fix",
