    "id": "31ed3665",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any\nSummary: Upgraded GEMM from 4x2/M2 (v4) to 4x4/M1 (unroll4) for out_ch<=64 path \u2014 2.6% improvement\nApproach: Added nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset_unroll4 with 4-channel x 4-pixel tiling using LMUL=M1. 16 M1 accumulators, 8 loads + 16 vd4dots per inner loop iteration. Compute-to-load ratio 2.0 (vs 1.33 for v4). Modified conv function to buffer 4 im2col pixels instead of 2.\nCycles before: 1769923\nCycles after: 1724015\nSpeedup: 1.03x\nPipeline insight: Inner loop: 8 vle8 + 16 vd4dots (M1). K=576 at VL=128 gives ~4.5 loop iters. With out_ch=16, only 4 channel groups. Reduction epilogue (16 vredsum + 12 vslideup + requantize) is significant overhead for small out_ch.\nLesson: 4x4/M1 upgrade gives modest 2.6% gain on asym_bias_any because: (1) v4 kernel was already good, (2) small out_ch=16 means few channel groups so reduction overhead dominates, (3) the asym contri_buf precomputation is a fixed cost. Larger out_ch would benefit more.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: conv, asym, GEMM, 4x4-tiling, vd4dots, M1",
