    "id": "4962865a",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_any\nSummary: Replaced ENA_TILING GEMM with im2col + runtime dispatch (unroll4 for col%4==0, 2-pixel for general) \u2014 4.37x speedup\nApproach: Same tiling\u2192im2col pattern but with runtime col_size%4 check since _any variant has no in_tensor_ch constraint. When divisible by 4, uses nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft_unroll4 (4-pixel); otherwise nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft (2-pixel). 5-region spatial partitioning. Perf test has ch=128 so unroll4 path is taken.\nCycles before: 2080991\nCycles after: 475951\nSpeedup: 4.37x\nPipeline insight: Same as _fast variants \u2014 tiling GEMM vectorizes col2=32 (12.5% VL util), unroll4 vectorizes K=1152 (~100% VL util)\nLesson: The _any (no channel constraint) variants can still use unroll4 with a runtime check. Cost is one branch per function call, negligible vs the 4x gain.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: tiling-to-im2col, unroll4, runtime-dispatch, sym-bias-any",
