    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any_dilated\nSummary: Runtime dispatch: groups==1 uses unroll4 (4-pixel batching) instead of v3 (2-pixel) \u2014 1.05x speedup\nApproach: When groups==1, batch 4 im2col columns and call nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset_unroll4 instead of 2-column nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset_v3. Required updating get_buffer_size to allocate 4 columns. Marginal improvement because perf test has out_tensor_ch=16 (only 4 channel groups per GEMM call).\nCycles before: 1822840\nCycles after: 1734821\nSpeedup: 1.05x\nPipeline insight: With out_tensor_ch=16 and rhs_cols=576, reduction (vredsum) dominates. GEMM kernel upgrade provides marginal benefit. Larger out_tensor_ch would benefit more.\nLesson: Asymmetric dilated conv with small out_tensor_ch (16) is reduction-dominated. GEMM kernel optimization has diminishing returns below ~32 output channels. Dilation support adds im2col overhead that further limits GEMM-side gains.\nOutcome: improved\nTags: asym, dilated, unroll4, runtime-dispatch, marginal",
