    "id": "8bb77f9f",
    "document": "Function: riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_RGB_sym_bias_fast\nSummary: Attempted im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft (2-pixel batching) to replace tiling GEMM \u2014 regressed 1.55x\nApproach: Replaced ENA_TILING block with im2col + nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft. 2-pixel batching. K=3*5*5=75.\nCycles before: 820793\nCycles after: 1269843\nSpeedup: 0.65x (regression)\nPipeline insight: K=75 too small for vd4dots at VLEN=1024: only 7.4% VL util for dot product (19/256 at e32/M8). Tiling GEMM vectorizes col2=256 output pixels at e16/M8 giving much better VL utilization.\nLesson: im2col + vd4dots GEMM does NOT work for RGB (ch_im_in=3) with small kernels because K=3*ker^2 is tiny. The tiling GEMM is better here because it vectorizes across output pixels not K. Also: nn_mat_mul_kernel_q7_bias_2sft_unroll4 silently truncates when col_size%4!=0.\nOutcome: regressed\nTags: RGB, im2col, small-K, tiling-GEMM, vd4dots-truncation",
    "metadata": {
      "cycles_before": "820793",
